<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/Forum72/HTML/000039.html">
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#400000"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#400000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Stormwaltz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Comic Sans MS, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, MS Sans">Greetings all. I know this forum has been, er, *quiet* for some time, and I know why. As Raze pointed out to me in an email earlier this week, you've run out of backstory to plumb the depths of.<P>Fear not! By creatively interpreting a couple of priority bugs ("This dungeon is way too hard." "Well, that's, uh... because it's supposed to be part of a quest!") we managed to get in some actual content in the midst of the endless bugfixes and balance tweaks. And there was much rejoicing.<P>The most readily obvious additions are the three heritage group libraries, which include a few stories you haven't read yet (there are more in the wings). Eri Izawa has wanted to get these in for quite some months now. My own addition to these are the translators, who can provide readable versions of old books and tablets you may find scattered across Dereth. If you've done my Drudge Note miniquest in Yaraq, it's the same mechanism. Each translator has their own era of expertise.<P>There are also a pair of new quests which provide more specific bits of backstory. One digs deep into the history of the Aluvians, and starts somewhere around Arwic. You'll have to be Level 20 or above to get into one of the dungeons. The other quest will give you a small glimpse of Dereth's history. <P>I have it on good authority that these have already been propped to the Zone. Enjoy, guys. Sorry we kept you hanging so long.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>- Chris<P>------------------<BR>** Turbine Entertainment Software doesn't know I said this. Shh.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
